About us

We have a vision that our communities will be safe and supported by fair and
ethical public institutions with a focus on those matters of highest threat to
the Queensland community. As an organisation we are committed to this vision
and as such our values of people, accountability, integrity, courage and
excellence underpin everything we do at the CCC.

What we offer

At the CCC our people have access to a range of employee benefits that promote
career development, enhance employee wellbeing and encourage a healthy and
balanced work and home life. When you join the CCC you can access the
following benefits:

• salary packaging  
• 12.75% superannuation  
• flexible work options, including working from home  
• access to paid parental leave  
• accrued time off  
• opportunity to purchase leave  
• 17.5% annual leave loading  
• health and wellbeing program  
• study assistance  
• access to a wide variety of training opportunities  
• free annual influenza vaccination  
• six star rated inner city location close to public transport

About you

For this role, we will consider how well you demonstrate:

  * Demonstrated knowledge and experience in enterprise and cloud application design, testing, implementation,   
support, and administration (SQL Server, Azure Applications, Power
Applications/Power Platform, Oracle an advantage).

  * Demonstrated knowledge in application development platforms and frameworks (.Net and Microsoft Devops an advantage) 
  * Demonstrated experience in leading an applications management function including change control, release   
management, continuous improvement, and project management.

  * Demonstrated ability to produce high quality reports, system, procedural, and user documentation. 
  * Proven ability to work in a team environment and develop effective working relationships with internal and external   
clients, team members, vendors, and end users.

  * Demonstrated commitment to business outcomes and service delivery in a customer-focused ICT environment 

How to apply

For more detailed information, including what is required to demonstrate your
suitability for the role, refer to the attached role description. Pre-
employment vetting forms a part of our selection process - you may be asked to
provide detailed personal particulars and private interests information. For
more information about our security vetting process please refer to How to
apply | CCC - Crime and Corruption Commission Queensland (
https://www.ccc.qld.gov.au/job-seekers/how-apply )

Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples are encouraged to apply.

